[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Local Housing Allowance Reforms [bold]&#xa0;
[normal]2.1
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]LHA
[normal] is a form of housing benefit paid to tenants in the private rented sector. Un
[normal]til April 2012, 
[normal]LHA
[normal] rates were calculated on a monthly basis based on actual rents in a local market
[normal].
[normal] 
[normal]Benefit levels would stay the same or even fall if rental markets remained 
[normal]steady
[normal], but if rents started rising due to market pressure, LHA rates would increase to ensure that low income private renting households could
[normal] 
[normal]find affordable accommodation
[normal]. 
[normal]The [bold]Welfare Reform Act broke this fundamental link between support for pr[bold]ivate re[bold]nters and actual rents by linking [bold]LHA rates to CPI inflation from April 2013. [bold]&#xa0;[bold]2.2
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]T
[normal]his means LHA rates will fall behind the actual cost of private renting as private rents have traditionally risen faster than inflation (from 1997-2007 rents increased by 
[normal]70 
[normal]per cent but CPI only rose by
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]20 per cent
[normal]). 
[normal]Li[bold]nking CPI to LHA would make a third of local authorities unaffordable to low income households by 2023[bold].[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]2.3
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The Minister for 
[normal]Welfare Reform acknowledged that
[normal] linking LHA to CPI 
[normal]risks
[normal] 
[normal]creating a “critical lack of
[normal] affordable housing”
[normal] and said
[normal] the Government was only committed to the measure until 2014-15
[normal], although the policy will automatically run on beyond the current spending review period
[normal]. He pledged to reconsider LHA rates at this point if they 
[normal]were 
[normal]out of ste
[normal]p with local rents
[normal], with the option to increase rates
[normal]. 
[normal]The Government must stick to this pledge. [bold]&#xa0;[bold]2.4
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]T[bold]he [bold]Welfare Up-rating Act[bold] [bold]2013 [bold]implemented[bold] a further cut, making it more likely that rents will outpace LHA.[bold] 
[normal]LHA
[normal] rates will
[normal] 
[normal]be up-rated by
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]a maximum of 
[normal]one 
[normal]per cent
[normal] 
[normal]in 2014-
[normal]15 and 2015-
[normal]16, even if rents or CPI are rising faster than this. 
[normal]The least affordable areas will be exempt, but DWP has so far released insufficient evidence of how this will be calculated and distributed
[normal],
[normal] nor have they addressed concerns about the impact in other areas.
[normal] 
[normal]T[bold]he more LHA rates are held down, the greater the risk that low income households won’t be able to find affordable housing[bold] in the private rented sector[bold]. [bold]&#xa0;
[normal]2.5
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]This is exacerbated further by
[normal] [bold]l
[normal]an
[normal]dlords
[normal]’
[normal] 
[normal]aversi
[normal]on
[normal] to hous
[normal]ing
[normal] tenants on benefi
[normal]ts. Successive reductions in h
[normal]ousing 
[normal]b
[normal]enefit 
[normal]have
[normal] made claimants more unattractive to 
[normal]landlords
[normal].
[normal] 
[normal]A Big L
[normal]ottery funded project by Shelter and Crisis
[normal] 
[normal]showed 
[normal]that 
[normal]landlords’ unwillingness to accept tenants on LHA is 
[normal]a major barrier to access
[normal] a private rented home
[normal]. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.6
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]In addition, separate 
[normal]e
[normal]vidence from Shelter
[normal] r
[normal]evealed how poorly the 
[normal]LHA 
[normal]changes have
[normal] been communicated. 
[normal]Claimants 
[normal]we spoke to
[normal] we
[normal]re 
[normal]extremely confused about what
[normal] was changing and 
[normal]what it meant
[normal] for them. We found a t
[normal]endency
[normal] for claimants
[normal] to conflate different chan
[normal]ges or to confuse
[normal] different
[normal] timetable
[normal]s.
[normal] 
[normal]F
[normal]or example, 
[normal]Universal Credit 
[normal](UC) 
[normal]and 
[normal]housing benefit
