[normal]T[bold]hose with legitimate reasons for needing the extra space including: [bold]&#xa0;[bold]4[bold]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Universal C[bold]redit – Alternative Payment Arrangements[bold]&#xa0;[bold]4.1
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Universal Credit (UC) will be paid as a ‘Standard Payment’ for the majority of claimants
[normal],
[normal] meaning claimants will receive a direct monthly payment to the household, inclusive 
[normal]of 
[normal]housing benefit
[normal].
[normal] 
[normal]Everyday money management is difficult for those on low i
[normal]ncomes and with complex needs. So, h
[normal]aving to m
[normal]anag
[normal]e
[normal] finances in this way 
[normal]may therefore 
[normal]lead to
[normal] arrears and ultimately eviction.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]4.2
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The DWP has announced 
[normal]welcome 
[normal]safeguards in the form of 
[normal]Alternative Payments Arrangements (APAs)
[normal] where 
[normal]the housing cost component of UC 
[normal]will
[normal] be paid direct to 
[normal]the 
[normal]landlord
[normal]. 
[normal]The APA proposals are welcome, but can be strengthened to ensure arrears are prevented in the first place.  [bold]&#xa0;[bold]4.3
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The goal for UC claimants in settled accommodation should be improving financial capability to move those who can[bold] to financial independence[bold].[bold] [bold]Each 
[normal]claimant should be assessed to 
[normal]identify whether they should begin on 
[normal]S
[normal]tandard 
[normal]P
[normal]ayments or an APA
[normal]. The assessment 
[normal]should 
[normal]consider needs beyond money management and debt and cover financial literacy, access to appropriate financial products, and other circum
[normal]stances such as drug and alcohol addiction and debts. The assessment should result in a
[normal]n
[normal] understanding of how long it might take the claimant to build financial capability and what support is required
[normal] 
[normal]to make Standard Payments a realistic goal. 
[normal]Households should have the option to self-refer for an assessment for APAs, at any time in their 
[normal]UC
[normal] application.
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]4.4
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Importantly, APAs should be used to prevent arrears occurring in the first place.[bold] [bold]Claimants who need A
[normal]PAs 
[normal]should be identified 
[normal]up-front 
[normal]in collaboration with landlords, 
[normal]Job Centre Plus, local authorities
[normal] and other
[normal] agencies to prevent them 
[normal]moving into arrears
[normal] – the Local Delivery Partnerships charged with making 
[normal]UC
[normal] work on the ground would be a natural lead for this
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]4.5
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]A[bold]ll homeless [bold]households i[bold]n [bold]t[bold]emporary [bold]a[bold]ccommodation (TA) should[bold] automat[bold]ically receive APAs [bold]to ensure the [bold]housing [bold]component of [bold]UC[bold] [bold]is paid to [bold]the [bold]landlord until they move into settled accommodation. [bold]This 
[normal]will ensure landlords receive rent and t
[normal]hat people 
[normal]in TA
[normal],
[normal] who in the
[normal] vast majority of cases have already been found homeless
[normal],
[normal] do not get evicted and become homeless again.  
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]4.6
